hh3cDot11sMesh.name: hh3cDot11sMesh

revisions.description: Modified to add new nodes and a new table.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cDot11sMesh.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDot11sMesh.description: The file defines a MIB to provide MESH configuration information. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Mesh A network consisting of two or more mesh points which communicate with each other via mesh services. Mesh Point (MP) An IEEE 802.11 entity that contains an IEEE 802.11-conformant medium access control (MAC) and physical layer (PHY) interface to the wireless medium (WM) that supports mesh services. Mesh Access Point (MAP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more access points. Mesh Portal Point (MPP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more portals. Mesh Link A link between two MPs.

hh3cDot11sMeshMkdID.name: hh3cDot11sMeshMkdID
hh3cDot11sMeshMkdID.description: This object represents the mesh key distributor identifier (MKD-ID). If the MKD-ID is not configured, the value is '00:00:00:00:00:00'.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflTable.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflTable
hh3cDot11sMeshPflTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh profile. A mesh profile is created and mapped to a MP so that it can provide mesh services to other MPs which have the same mesh ID. When the mesh profile is enabled, all of the object in this table can not be modified except hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable. The mesh profile can not be deleted when it is bound with the radio.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflEntry.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflEntry
hh3cDot11sMeshPflEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a mesh profile.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflIndex.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflIndex
hh3cDot11sMeshPflIndex.description: This object represents the index of the mesh profile.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID
hh3cDot11sMeshPflMeshID.description: This object represents the mesh ID of the mesh profile. The string length of this object is zero when the mesh ID is not configured. If the mesh ID is not configured, hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum
hh3cDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.description: This object represents the specified mesh interface number binding to the mesh profile. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed. If the mesh interface is not specified, the value of hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive
hh3cDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.description: This object represents the mesh link keep-alive interval.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate
hh3cDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.description: This object represents the link backhaul rate.

hh3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.name: hh3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable
hh3cDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh key distributor (MKD) service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The MKD service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The MKD service for the mesh profile is disabled.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable
hh3cDot11sMeshPflEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The mesh profile is disabled.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus
hh3cDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyTable.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyTable
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyTable.description: This table is used to configure MP policy. There is 'default_mp_plcy' on system by default and its index is 1. The 'default_mp_plcy' can not be deleted or modified. The MP policy can not be deleted when it is applied to a radio. It can not be modified when it is applied to an enabled radio.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a MP policy.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyIndex.description: This object represents the MP policy index.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyName.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyName
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyName.description: This object represents the MP policy name. MP policy can not be created with name 'a', 'al', 'all' or 'default_mp_plcy'. Modification is not supported.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.description: This object indicates whether the link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'true': The link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'false': The link initiation for the MP policy is disabled.

hh3cDot11sMlspEnable.name: hh3cDot11sMlspEnable
hh3cDot11sMlspEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh link switch protocol (MLSP) is enabled. 'true': MLSP is enabled. 'false': MLSP is disabled.

hh3cDot11sProbReqInterval.name: hh3cDot11sProbReqInterval
hh3cDot11sProbReqInterval.description: This object represents the probe request interval.

hh3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable.name: hh3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable
hh3cDot11sRoleAuthEnable.description: This object indicates whether the device can play as the role of an authenticator.

hh3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.name: hh3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI
hh3cDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.description: This object represents the link-hold receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

hh3cDot11sLinkHoldTime.name: hh3cDot11sLinkHoldTime
hh3cDot11sLinkHoldTime.description: This object represents the link-hold time.

hh3cDot11sSwitchMargin.name: hh3cDot11sSwitchMargin
hh3cDot11sSwitchMargin.description: This object represents the link-switch margin.

hh3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.name: hh3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI
hh3cDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.description: This object represents the link saturation receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

hh3cDot11sLinkRateMode.name: hh3cDot11sLinkRateMode
hh3cDot11sLinkRateMode.description: This object represents the rate mode of the mesh link.

hh3cDot11sMaxLinkNum.name: hh3cDot11sMaxLinkNum
hh3cDot11sMaxLinkNum.description: This object represents the maximum number of the mesh link.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11sMlspCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11sMlspCfgTable
hh3cDot11sMlspCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure MLSP proxy MAC address. Only if the specified MP policy is modifiable and the MLSP is enabled, the row of this table can be created and deleted. The row of this table can not be modified.

hh3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry
hh3cDot11sMlspCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of MLSP proxy MAC address.

hh3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex.name: hh3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex
hh3cDot11sMlspProxyIndex.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address index.

hh3cDot11sMlspProxyMac.name: hh3cDot11sMlspProxyMac
hh3cDot11sMlspProxyMac.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address.

hh3cDot11sMlspRowStatus.name: hh3cDot11sMlspRowStatus
hh3cDot11sMlspRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hh3cDot11sRadioCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11sRadioCfgTable
hh3cDot11sRadioCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified radio.

hh3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry
hh3cDot11sRadioCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified radio.

hh3cDot11sMeshPflMap.name: hh3cDot11sMeshPflMap
hh3cDot11sMeshPflMap.description: This object represents the number of the mesh profile mapped to the specified radio. The value is zero when the radio is not binding mesh profile.

hh3cDot11sMpPlcyMap.name: hh3cDot11sMpPlcyMap
hh3cDot11sMpPlcyMap.description: This object represents the index of the MP policy mapped to the specified radio. The MP policy is 'default_mp_plcy' when the radio is not binding user-defined MP policy. The index of 'default_mp_plcy' is 1. This object can not be modified when the radio is enabled.

hh3cDot11sAPCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11sAPCfgTable
hh3cDot11sAPCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified AP.

hh3cDot11sAPCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11sAPCfgEntry
hh3cDot11sAPCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified AP.

hh3cDot11sPortalEnable.name: hh3cDot11sPortalEnable
hh3cDot11sPortalEnable.description: This object indicates whether the portal service is enabled. 'true': The portal service is enabled. 'false': The portal service is disabled.

hh3cDot11sWDSPeerMacTable.description: This table is used to configure wireless distribution system (WDS). The row of this table can not be modified.
